{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #1100: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. If $1=d_1<\\cdots<d_{\\tau(n)}=n$ are the divisors of $n$, then let $\\tau_\\perp(n)$ count the number of $i$ for which $(d_i,d_{i+1})=1$.\n\nIs it true that $\\tau_\\perp(n)/\\omega(n)\\to \\infty$ for almost all $n$? Is it true that\\[\\tau_\\perp(n)< \\exp((\\log n)^{o(1)})\\]for all $n$?\n\nLet\\[g(k) = \\max_{\\omega(n)=k}\\tau_\\perp(n),\\]where $\\omega(n)$ counts the number of distinct prime divisors of $n$, and $n$ is restricted to squarefree integers. Determine the growth of $g(k)$. Prize: no. OEIS: A325864. Tags: divisors, number theory.","id":"vf_1e44975b197f6a9b","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: FC 1100 (PR #3422) [in-pr] https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures/pull/3422.","id":"vf_35c6c13c84185be5","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Hosted Lean proof: plby proof of 1100 (state partial) https://github.com/plby/lean-proofs/blob/main/src/v4.29.1/ErdosProblems/Erdos1100.lean.","id":"vf_7377ea46e6507096","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/1100.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_1e44975b197f6a9b","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:1100","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_35c6c13c84185be5","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:1100","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"